divs: Sighting DetailsAt about 10:30 p.m. us and our two friends were outside smoking and looking up at the stars, when my husband seen this bright light, thinking it was a sattelite.��� So we all looked up and realized it was moving to quick to be a sattelite.��� It was very low, lower than a high flying aircraft.��� It had no blinking lights, like an airplane or helicopter, and it was completely quiet.��� We continued to watch it go off to the east and all of a sudden it was just gone, like someone turned the light off. Me and my girlfriend didn't know what to think, and my husband and her boyfriend couldn't quit staring at the sky, waiting for it to come back.��� We didn't know what we just saw, but we thought it was crazy.
Summary: Bright light moving west to east with no sound.
